Weekly visual project - 2019/12/21
The excerpt  When we intend to solve a problem consciously, we process information in a linear, logical fashion. But when ideas call to each other on their own, without our leading them down a straight and narrow path, unexpected combinations may come into being.
Excerpt From: Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi. &ldquo;Creativity.&rdquo;
